✨Postpartum Hair Loss✨
Today we dive into the reality of Postpartum hair shedding. 
It’s a topic I get asked about often. The time to recovery varies on each individual, depending on hormones and genetics.
In some people it’s three months, in some people it’s six months. Occasionally it can last an entire year.
Proper nutrition is essential to managing your postpartum hair loss, and stimulating the hair follicle is key to encouraging the hair to grow back after the shed. 
Tune in to learn more, and check out stories to hear my answers to your questions!

HAPPY FULL MOON 🌕 
How I Hairemony these days 💕
The Full Moon is a powerful time to do your favorite hair rituals. This moon phase focuses on what it is we would like to shed, release, or let go of what no longer supports our highest intentions.
It is a great time for hair strengthening and thickening...think of it as the “Werewolf effect” the full moon helps hair grow fast, thick, long and luscious!

Here’s a little 🌝 ritual for you- 

✨Set an intention for your hair ritual
This can be as simple as focusing on growth

✨Clear your space and aura
A really great way to get grounded, calm the nervous system and create more of a sacred space for your hair ritual

✨Choose an oil best for you and your hair type/texture
Our favorites are the LTS Jojoba and Treatment of course, but any oil you love

✨Massage deeply into the scalp
Give your self some love and attention, massage long enough to feel the scalp stimulated, maybe even tingling

✨Sleep in the oil and Shampoo out 2x, follow through with our Repair Masque for extra love, rinse and enjoy the Full Moon transformation 👌🏼

Treatment vs Repair Masque

❄️ Winter ❄️ haircare tips for healthy hair and scalp..

Temperatures are dropping and that winter dryness is starting to disrupt our scalp and strands! 
I know we are technically in fall, but I do believe starting this winter regimen will help combat the dryness and protect the hair as we move into colder, drier climates.. 

Here are my tips for maintaining your optimal hair health for this upcoming season.. 

Oils! 
Leave in Oil Treatments once a week- hydration is so important

Using serums/oils on ends help combat frizz and static

Internal oils- adding to soups, chais, coffee, are super beneficial 

Moisture-
Make sure to condition every time you wash and incorporate a deep conditioning Masque into you regimen weekly 

Protect-
It’s important to protect the hair from the elements- cover with a wrap, hat, beannie to minimize exposure

Styling-
Wash less often if you can- use dry shampoo to prolong time between washes

Style less- ideal to leave natural and not use heat styling tools, but if necessary, opt for a style that will last- like a weekly blow out

Invest in-
A good humidifier especially for night time
A good shower filter to help protect the hair

Trims are always good, but I don’t think it’s necessary to cut often- there are ways to prevent dry and damaged ends, so getting a good cut seasonally is key, but a good cut should last, and if you start incorporating all of these tips, you won’t need to cut so often. 

Hope this guide helps achieve your best hair throughout this winter!

SHAMPOO 101
Ok- I seriously want to do a class on this, as it’s a topic that comes up frequently with many of my clients…
Specifically with our Shampoo, since we do not water it down- a little goes a long way! If you use it properly, you’ll not only save your hair from damage, but you’ll save some product (and money too!).

🫧 Shampoo Steps 🫧 
1- Rinse your hair thoroughly with lukewarm water (hot can cause damage)
2- Pour a small amount of the La Tierra Sagrada Shampoo into your palm. Rub hands together to create a light foam
3- Apply the foam directly to the hair and scalp, but starting at the hair line and working your way back to the nape
4- Focus on roots mostly, and the hair closest to the scalp, gently massaging with the fingertips
5- Lightly lather the ends of the hair by picking up the hair, not rubbing together- this creates more friction on wet, vulnerability hair, which could be leading to damage, frizz, or static
6- Rinse thoroughly to remove all soap from the hair. Repeat all of the above again if you’re removing the La Tierra Sagrada Treatment, other hair oil, or wash less frequently
